==Galician==
[[File:Serra de São Mamede com uma giesta a sobrepor-se.JPG|thumb|''xesta'']]
===Etymology===
From Old Galician and {{inh|gl|roa-opt|gẽesta}}, from {{inh|gl|la|genesta|t=broom}}. Cognate with {{cog|pt|gesta}} and {{cog|es|hiniesta}}.
===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|gl|/ˈʃɛsta̝/}}
===Noun===
{{gl-noun|f}}
# [[broom]] ({{taxlink|Cytisus scoparius|species|ver=191028}})
#* '''1408''', José Luis Novo Cazón (ed.), ''El priorato santiaguista de Vilar de Donas en la Edad Media (1194-1500)''. A Coruña: Fundación Barrié, page 318:
#*: ''que façades a dicta metade da dicta casa de pedra e de madeyra e de '''giestas''' e de colmo''
#*:: you should build that half house with stone and wood and '''brooms''' and thatch
# [[broom]] {{gloss|tool}}
